Danger zone
“My family has been a target since I declared my intention to take on President Museveni three years. I decided to yield to the requests from my friends abroad and ship my children out of this danger zone because they are minors and not voters,” he said, while challenging the regime in Kampala to engage him and not his children. 
“My focus is to ensure they don't kidnap the minors and try to use them to coerce me into subjugation!”
He dismissed claims that by taking his children out, he was unpatriotic and a coward, or that the act was a crime arguing that Mr Museveni has also in similar situation when shipped his family to Sweden when the civil war that catapulted him to power was intense.
“Leave my children out of this... they are minors. Come for me and my wife, we are the adults. I am the candidate. I am here to face you,” 
Mr Kyagulanyi’s music rival Mr Moses Ssali alias Bebe Cool was one of the first people to share the photos of the children on social media as they travelled out of the country, attracting condemnation from Ugandans on Twitter for exploiting the minor’s helplessness for political reasons



