UPC was founded by Milton Obote and is one of the political parties that founded the modern Uganda state alongside the Democratic Party and Kabaka Yekka. Coincidentally, UPC is led by Jimmy Akena who is the late Obote’s son.
Mr Museveni seized power after he waged a grueling five-year gorilla war against the UPC regime.



