For the first time, Dr Kizza Busigye, who has come to symbolise opposition against Mr Museveni and the brutality of his regime in previous elections, refused to participate in the presidential election, arguing that it was an exercise in futility.
Instead, Mr Peter Amuriat was nominated to carry the Forum for Democratic Change ticket in the race.
Mr Amuriat had his convoy shot at by police in Kitagwenda District on Wednesday. Witnesses account suggest that a police officer aimed his gun at his speeding car but the bullet missed, hitting the escort vehicle instead.
It shattered the windscreen, but nobody was injured.
The head of Mr Amuriat’s security team arrested the police officer and surrendered him at Mahyoro Police Station where he was detained.
Yesterday, he campaigned in in Kagadi, Kibale and Kakumiro districts.
Others in the race are former President Museveni’s Security Minister Henry Tumukunde, who is running as an independent, former Army Commander Mugisha Muntu, who is the flag bearer of the Alliance of National Transformation and Norbert Mao of the Democratic Party.
Others are 24-year-old John Katumba (Independent), Willy Mayambala (Independent), Fred Mwesigye, journalist Joseph Kabuleta (Independent) and Nancy Kalembe who is the only woman in the race. 



